Returns an enumerator that can iterate through the collection.
trans-unit.target: 컬렉션을 반복할 수 있는 열거자를 반환 합니다.

trans-unit.source: Enumerators only allow reading the data in the collection.
trans-unit.target: 열거자는 컬렉션의 데이터 읽기를 허용 합니다.

trans-unit.source: Enumerators cannot be used to modify the underlying collection.
trans-unit.target: 내부 컬렉션을 수정 하 여 열거자를 사용할 수 없습니다.

trans-unit.source: Initially, the enumerator is positioned before the first item in the collection.
trans-unit.target: 처음에 열거자는 컬렉션의 첫 번째 항목 앞에 배치 됩니다.

trans-unit.source: At this position, calling <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.Current%2A> throws an exception.

Therefore, you must call <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.MoveNext%2A> to advance the enumerator to the first item of the collection before reading the value of <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.Current%2A>.
trans-unit.target: 따라서 <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.MoveNext%2A>하 여 열거자 <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.Current%2A>.</xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.Current%2A> 의 값을 읽기 전에 컬렉션의 첫 번째 항목을</xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.MoveNext%2A> 호출 해야 합니다.

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.Current%2A> returns the same object until either <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.Reset%2A> is called.
<xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.MoveNext%2A> sets <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.Current%2A> to the next item.

After the end of the collection is passed, the enumerator is positioned after the last item in the collection, and calling <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.MoveNext%2A> returns `false`.
trans-unit.target: 컬렉션의 끝이 전달 된 후 열거자는 컬렉션의 마지막 항목 뒤에 배치 하 고 호출 되 <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.MoveNext%2A>반환 `false`.</xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: If the last call to <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.MoveNext%2A> returned `false`, calling <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.Current%2A> throws an exception.

To set <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.Current%2A> to the first item of the collection again, you can call <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.Reset%2A> followed by <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.MoveNext%2A>.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.Current%2A>다시, 컬렉션의 첫 번째 항목 호출 하면 <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.Reset%2A>그 뒤 <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.MoveNext%2A>.</xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.MoveNext%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.Reset%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.Current%2A> 설정 하려면

trans-unit.source: An enumerator remains valid as long as the collection remains unchanged.
trans-unit.target: 열거자는 컬렉션이 변경 되지으로 유효한 상태를 유지 합니다.

trans-unit.source: If changes are made to the collection, such as adding, modifying or deleting items, the enumerator is irrecoverably invalidated and the next call to <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.Reset%2A> throws an <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>.
trans-unit.target: 열거자는 무효화 및 <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.MoveNext%2A> <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.Reset%2A> <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>.</xref:System.InvalidOperationException> throw</xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.Reset%2A> 또는</xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.MoveNext%2A> 을 다음에 호출할 등 추가, 수정 또는 삭제 항목 컬렉션을 변경 하는 경우

trans-unit.source: If the collection is modified between <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.MoveNext%2A> and <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.Current%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.Current%2A> will return the item that it is set to, even if the enumerator is already invalidated.
trans-unit.target: 사이 컬렉션이 수정 되는 경우 <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.MoveNext%2A>및 <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.Current%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.Current%2A>열거자가 이미 무효로 되 었 하는 경우에로 설정 되어 있는 항목을 반환 합니다.</xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Media.DoubleCollection.Enumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: The enumerator does not have exclusive access to the collection; therefore, enumerating through a collection is intrinsically not a thread-safe procedure.
trans-unit.target: 열거자는 컬렉션에 배타적으로 액세스가 없습니다. 따라서 컬렉션을 열거 것은 본질적으로 스레드로부터 안전한 프로시저가 아닙니다.

trans-unit.source: Even when a collection is synchronized, other threads could still modify the collection, which causes the enumerator to throw an exception.
trans-unit.target: 컬렉션이 동기화 되어 있을 때 다른 스레드에서 수 수정할 열거자에서 예외가 발생 하는 컬렉션입니다.

trans-unit.source: To guarantee thread safety during enumeration, you can either lock the collection during the entire enumeration or catch the exceptions resulting from changes made by other threads.
trans-unit.target: 열거 동안 스레드 보안을 보장 하려면 전체 열거 동안 컬렉션을 잠글 하거나 다른 스레드에서 변경 된 내용으로 인해 발생 한 예외를 catch 합니다.
